<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--StreetsweeperFlees     05-25 0172</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Streetsweeper Flees,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>East German Flees To West In Street-Sweeping Vehicle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An East German cleaning a road near
the West German border suddenly gunned the engine of his
street-sweeping vehicle and safely escaped from his communist
homeland, police said.
   The 62-year-old man fled Wednesday as two East German border
soldiers were overseeing his work, but there were no reports of any
shots being fired, said a statement by the Bavarian border police.
   The worker, who was not identified, was operating the
streetcleaner on East German turf near the West German checkpoint
at Eussenhausen, about 75 miles northeast of Frankfurt.
   According to Bavarian border police, he suddenly stepped on the
gas and savely drove the machine onto Bavarian soil.
   The man's wife has been visiting in West Germany and he decided
to join her after she told him she would not be returning to
communist East Germany, the police statement said.
   The statement said West German officials planned to return the
street-cleaning machine to East German authorities.
</TEXT>
