<HEAD>Teens Changed Electronic Sign to Offer Free Gas, Authorities Say</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Vermilion is cq in 3rd graf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DANVILLE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Teen-age hackers penetrated a truck stop
computer and changed an electronic sign so that it promised free
gasoline.
   The three failed to get into the computers of some other
businesses, but they did embarrass Trucker's World Truck Stop about
a month ago.
   ``They changed the message to read `Free fillup and drive
away,''' said Pat Hartshorn, Vermilion County chief investigator.
The sign also was programmed with a vulgar phrase.
   No one took any gas, authorities said.
   Prosecutors have not decided whether to charge the teen-agers.
Authorities declined to identify them or say where they are from.
