<HEAD>GM-Beretta Sign Trademark Agreement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The battle of the Berettas ended today with an
exchange of guns and a car.
   Pier Giuseppe Beretta, chairman of the weapons maker Fabbrica
D'Armi Pietro Beretta S.p.A., and General Motors Corp. Chairman
Roger Smith signed an agreement allowing GM to use the Beretta name
for the Chevrolet Beretta car.
