<FIRST>r i AM-HumanGoldfish     05-25 0336</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Human Goldfish,0347</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Has Lived For a Week in a Glass Box</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MATTI HUUHTANEN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HELSINKI, Finland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reijo Kela awakens, performs his
morning hygiene rituals, eats breakfast and dresses in a black suit
and bow tie.
   Sounds normal enough, but Kela is doing it all in a glass box in
a public square downtown, in front of hundreds of curious
pedestrians.
   Kela, a famous Finnish dancer and performance artist, is
performing a week-long modern dance called ``Cityman.''
   Since May 19, Kela has danced, slept, ate, bathed in a
see-through bathtub, and gone to the toilet in his 5-yard-square
booth.
   Kela made no announcement before turning himself into a human
goldfish, and no one is quite sure what he's doing there. He has a
telephone, which he refuses to answer. He reportedly plans to
emerge Friday.
   Music from commercial radio stations blares through a speaker,
interrupted occasionally by recordings of Kela announcing that he
is ``the Cityman. The best. Everybody wants to make love to me.''
   The booth, which has glass on two sides and two boarded walls,
is equipped with a mattress, sleeping bag, two laundry baskets, a
stereo and a red rose beside his bed.
   Occasionally, Kela is joined by one of the seven women who
belong to his dance troupe.
   In his recorded message he promises to ``win over every single
woman who passes by.''
   Pedestrians often walk by quickly with a bemused comment or an
embarrassed smile. ``This must be the answer to the housing
problem,'' one Finn was heard telling his wife.
   Kela also has fans. Some have drawn hearts in lipstick and
written his name on the glass wall, and others have left flowers.
   Not everyone is amused. A TV crew left angrily after hours of
waiting to shoot while Kela, stretched out on a bear rug in midday,
refused to move.
   One young girl complained: ``I've come a long way to see him
because I've liked his dances _ but he hasn't budged.''
</TEXT>
