sted on the surface. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A nuclear-powered attack submarine got stuck on
a reef during underwater exercises four miles offshore but freed
itself after four hours and returned to base under its own power,
the Navy said today.
   No injuries were reported among the Grunard's 135-member crew,
and the submarine sustained no apparent hull damage and no damage
to its nuclear reactor in Tuesday's grounding, Navy spokeswoman Lt.
Sonja Hedley said.
