<FIRST>u a PM-LukensTrial 2ndLd-Writethru a0573 05-25 0799</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lukens Trial, 2nd Ld - Writethru, a0573,0817</SECOND>
<HEAD>Congressman Denied Having Sex With Girl</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 8 grafs to UPDATE with investigator's testimony,
defense resting; PICKS UP 5th graf pvs, ``She was ...'</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto CO3</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BETH GRACE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Donald Lukens denied having sex with
a teen-age girl but did offer her mother a job during a telephone
conversation secretly recorded by the FBI and police and played for
the jury today.
   On the tape, played on the fourth day of Lukens' trial on
charges of contributing to the delinquency or unruliness of a
minor, the congressman told the girl's mother that her daughter had
been calling, and he asked that she stop.
   Later, a private investigator J.D. Caudill testified that
Lukens, who is divorced, admitted to him in January that he had sex
with the girl and knew she was underage. The investigator had been
hired by Lukens' then-attorney.
   ``He admitted that he did have sexual intercourse with Rosie
Coffman,'' Caudill testified.
   After the prosecution completed its case, the defense rested
without calling any witnesses.
   Defense attorney Thomas Tyack said he would have introduced
testimony about the girl's juvenile record if the judge had not
ruled such evidence inadmissable.
   If convicted of the misdemeanor, Lukens, a 58-year-old
Republican, could be sentenced to six months in jail and fined
$1,000.
   During the taped Nov. 11 telephone conversation, Anna Coffman
told the congressman that her 17-year-old daughter, Rosie, had
confessed to her that she had sex with Lukens on Nov. 6.
   ``She was there with Mercedes. What Mercedes and I did was
private. Your daughter had nothing to do with it,'' Lukens replied,
according to the tape.
   Mercedes was the name used by Ms. Coffman's friend, Michelle
Foster, then 19, who had invited Ms. Coffman to Lukens' apartment
that night.
   Lukens also asked Mrs. Coffman whether she was still
``interested in the job.'' Mrs. Coffman testified earlier that
Lukens made her a job offer during a meeting between at a Columbus
fast-food restaurant earlier in the day.
   On Tuesday, Ms. Coffman testified that she had sex with Lukens
on the eve of her 17th birthday and lied to Lukens, telling him she
was turning 19 years old. But Ms. Coffman said she also gave him
her real birthdate _ Nov. 7, 1971.
   ``I told him my birthday was the next day,'' Ms. Coffman
testified. ``He asked me how old I was going to be. I told him 19
years old ... but I gave him my real birthdate. I wasn't thinking.
He wrote it down on a yellow tablet.''
   She also testified Wednesday in Domestic Relations Court that
Lukens gave her $40 and a birthday gift after she had sex with him
that night. Ms. Coffman also said Lukens made several racial slurs
during the evening.
   Lukens is white. Ms. Coffman is black.
   WSYX TV reporter Ted Hart continued testifying today on his role
in the videotaping of a Nov. 11 meeting between Lukens and Rosie
Coffman's mother at the fast-food restaurant.
   Hart, who arranged the taping, told the jury he never heard Mrs.
Coffman ask for money from Lukens. But he said he heard Lukens
offer to help Mrs. Coffman find a job after she explained that her
daughter was underage.
   Lukens has said Mrs. Coffman attempted to extort money from him
in exchange for her silence. Mrs. Coffman has testifed, however,
that Lukens tried to bribe her with an offer of help in finding a
government job.
   Lukens, who is divorced, served in Congress for two terms in the
1960s, then in the Ohio Senate before returning to Congress in
1986, representing the Middletown area in southwest Ohio.
   Rosie Coffman testified that she went to Lukens' apartment to
talk to him about their first meeting, in 1985. Under
cross-examination, however, she admitted she never did discuss the
1985 incident with Lukens and that she did not recall for sure
whether she told Lukens she was 18 or 19.
   The congressman appeared agitated as Ms. Coffman described in
graphic detail their alleged sexual encounter. At one point, he
balled up both fists and hit his knees. At other times, he shook
his head and scowled.
   Ms. Coffman said she and a friend, Michelle Foster, visited
Lukens at his home Nov. 6. Ms. Foster was 19 at the time.
   ``My friend Michelle gave me a call. She said she had met a
congressman. She called him by the name of `Buz,''' Ms. Coffman
said, referring to Lukens' nickname.
   At his apartment, she said she performed oral sex on Lukens and
had intercourse with him twice. She said Lukens gave her two $20
bills and paid Ms. Foster $30 even though Ms. Coffman said her
friend did not have sex with him.
</TEXT>
