<HEAD>Swap of Car for Guns Seals Beretta-Beretta Deal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One side was given a Chevy and the other received
a pair of hunting guns, and an agreement was signed Thursday
settling a name dispute between General Motors Corp. and a famous
Italian weapons maker.
   GM Chairman Roger Smith and Pier Giuseppe Beretta, chairman of
Fabbrica D'Armi Pietro Beretta S.p.A., exchanged the products
during a ceremony in Italy putting to rest a suit brought nearly a
year ago, the company announced.
