<FIRST>r f BC-USAirLogo     05-25 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-USAir Logo,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Airline Changing Image</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USAir is swapping its red and brown logo for a
more refreshing red, white and blue one, airline officials said
Wednesday.
   USAir will scrape the old paint from all its 429 jets within the
next two years and replace it with a new logo that includes the
airline's name in the new colors on the fuselage.
   The tail will be painted blue with ``USAir'' in white letters
between red stripes.
   USAir Chairman Edwin Colodny said it will cost $7,000 to paint
each plane.
   ``We all need to refresh ourselves periodically with a new suit
of clothes or a new dress,'' Colodny told reporters and airline
workers at Greater Pittsburgh International Airport.
   The present logo was designed in 1975.
</TEXT>
