<HEAD>Production Down This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
233,236 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
248,552, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 245,902 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 147,404 cars this week,
compared with 159,479 a week ago and 162,088 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,832,
compared with last week's 89,073 and last year's 83,814.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,877 cars this week, up from
18,001 a week ago but down from last year's 16,152.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,849,
compared with 16,905 a week ago and 16,152 in the same week last
year.
