<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Sony     05-25 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Sony,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sony Reports Robust Revenue, Profit Growth</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sony Corp. said Thursday its fourth-quarter profit
jumped 56.1 percent and its annual earnings nearly doubled, boosted
by higher sales in all of its electronics divisions.
   After-tax income totaled 14.4 billion yen, or about $109
million, in the three months ended March 31, up from 9.2 billion
yen a year earlier.
   Sales were 539 billion yen, or about $4.1 billion, in the fourth
quarter, up from 407 billion yen a year earlier.
   For the full year, net income grew to 72.5 billion yen, or $549
million, up from 37 billion yen the prior year.
   Sales for the full year totaled 2.15 trillion yen, or $16.2
billion, up from the prior year's 1.56 trillion yen.
   Sony said revenue growth reflected strong worldwide demand for
major consumer electronics products, such as video cassette
recorders and audio equipment including compact disk players.
</TEXT>
