<FIRST>r f BC-Sears-Superstore     05-25 0187</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Sears-Superstore,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Retailer Unveils New Men's Store</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sears, Roebuck and Co., trying to revise its
image and revive sales, on Thursday introduced a men's ``superstore
within a store'' at a suburban outlet.
   Michael Bozic, chairman of Sears Merchandise Group, said the
department will have six different shops with more than 70 national
and Sears brands.
   The shops are young men's sportswear, activewear, classic
sportwear, big and tall, men's furnishings and men's workwear.
   They opened at a Sears in Aurora, west of Chicago, and will
spread through the nation next year, the company said.
   ``We are now examining nearly 400 markets,'' Bozic said. ``And
for each market with the appropriate potential, Sears will install
the superstore in sizes ranging up to 16,500 square feet.''
   Bozic said it is the third in its program. The first, Brand
Central, a home electronics and appliances store, was introduced in
18 Indiana stores last year. The second, Kids &amp; More, was
introduced in a store in Merrillville, Ind., and another in Chicago.
   Similar formats are being developed for women's fashions,
automotive, home improvements and home fashions, Bozic said.
</TEXT>
